org.safs.net

Enum IHttpRequest.Key

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<IHttpRequest.Key>
      • org.safs.net.IHttpRequest.Key
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<IHttpRequest.Key>
    Enclosing interface:
    IHttpRequest

    public static enum IHttpRequest.Key
extends java.lang.Enum<IHttpRequest.Key>
    The enumeration represents some of XMLHttpRequest Object Properties, such as "status", "statusText", "responseText" etc. and some other strings like "responseHeaders", "requestHeaders".
    They will be used as keys in Map result returned by IHttpRequest.execute(HttpCommand, String, boolean, Map, String).
    The enumeration has a method value(), which can return the string format.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • READY_STATE

        public static final IHttpRequest.Key READY_STATE
        'readyState' 
         
 Holds the status of the XMLHttpRequest. Changes from 0 to 4:
 0: request not initialized
 1: server connection established
 2: request received
 3: processing request
 4: request finished and response is ready
        See Also:
        XMLHttpRequest.AjaxReadyState
